<TITLE> Schoolboy slaughtered in Jamalpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jamalpur, Mar 24 (bdnews24.com)  A school boy was slaughtered by some unidentified assailants on Tuesday night at Bazaripara area of Jamalpur town. The victim, Shah Jamal Islam Sadhin, was a student of class 10 at Jamalpur High School. Sadhin's father Saiful Islam, a businessman of Bazaripara, told journalists that Sadhin stepped out of their house after power outage at around 11 p.m. to gossip with two of his friends. It was around that time the assailants attacked him, Sadhin's father said. He was immediately taken to the hospital, where doctors pronounced him dead. Saiful said that some youths of Nayapara area were responsible for the murder, although he said he had no clue as to why they did it. Abdul Motin, the OC of Jamalpur Police station, said police was investigating the case. bdn
